  "text": "Low bone BMD may be a factor in IF failure. Although not statistically significant, the subgroup analysis for undisplaced fractures (Table 3) showed a hazard ratio of 6 for low BMD as compared to 0.8 for the whole group (Table 2) . For undisplaced femoral neck fractures, there should be a normal blood supply and good bone contact between the bone fragments. Compared to displaced fractures, the major reason for failure might lie in the stability. Osteoporosis appears to affect the anchorage of screws [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and could therefore be a reason for lower stability in the undisplaced fracture, and hence failure.",
